        "title": "Is there a way to make an array truly private in Java?",
        "body": "<p>If I do something like<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private int[] myPrivateArray;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and have a getter that returns the array, then the array contents can be modified from outside the class, which sort of defeats the purpose of making it private.<\/p>\n",
